## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [CS16034]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Embryo fails to develop beyond the globular stage.  Consisten and severe developmental arrest at the mid-globular stage, resulting in a slightly irregular embryo proper consisting of 32-64 cells.  Arrested embryos persist in this early arrested stage into late-stage seeds, without any apparent further growth.
   - [CS16034]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;embryo defective; developmental arrest of mutant embryos
   - [nuwa-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;All pollen grains of heterozygote plant are viable. Mutation does not affect male gametophyte viability.
   - [nuwa-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;embryo lethal.
   - [nuwa-2]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;All pollen grains of heterozygote plant are viable. Mutation does not affect male gametophyte viability.
   - [nuwa-2]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;embryo lethal.
